= Description =
This suite of scripts and configuration files helps you make "ready to run" containers.
= How it works =
Deployement of new container is done in 2 steps :
 - create a template (minimal distribution ready to be containerized)
 - create the container
= Install =
I use /lxc to store containers and lxc-provider
If you want to use another location modify (one line each) :
./lxc/bin/lxc-provider
./lxc/bin/lxc-template
./lxc/etc/general.conf
to reflect the new location

I will suppose you use /lxc too:

 tar xvzf lxc-provider -C /

= Usage =
To install a debian lenny:
 - Check network settings in /lxc/etc/provisionning/net.conf
 - set PATH
# export PATH="${PATH}:/lxc/bin"
 - Mount cgroup
# mkdir /cgroup
# mount -t cgroup none /cgroup
 - Make your ethernet bridge is up
# brctl addbr br0
 - set ip address for your bridge
# ifconfig br0 10.0.0.254 netmask 255.0.0.0
 - Let's make a template
# lxc-template create debian/debian/lenny
 - make the container
# lxc-provider create debian/debian/lenny -i 10.0.0.100 -n mycontainer
 - start the container
# lxc-start -n mycontainer

= Available templating conf =
 - debian/debian/lenny
 - debian/ubuntu/hardy
 - debian/ubuntu/intrepid
 - debian/ubuntu/jaunty
 - debian/ubuntu/karmic

